</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput " data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h2 id="4---Confidence-Intervals-for-$AR(p)$-Inference">4 - Confidence Intervals for $AR(p)$ Inference<a class="anchor-link" href="#4---Confidence-Intervals-for-$AR(p)$-Inference">&#182;</a></h2><h3 id="4.1-Normality-Assumption">4.1 Normality Assumption<a class="anchor-link" href="#4.1-Normality-Assumption">&#182;</a></h3><p>Assume:
$$
\epsilon \sim \mathcal{N}(0, \sigma^2 I)
$$</p>
<p>Then:
$$
\hat{a} = (X^T X)^{-1} X^T x \sim \mathcal{N}\left(a, \ \sigma^2 (X^T X)^{-1}\right)
$$</p>
<hr>
<h3 id="4.2-Variance-Estimation">4.2 Variance Estimation<a class="anchor-link" href="#4.2-Variance-Estimation">&#182;</a></h3><p>Estimate noise variance:
$$
\hat{\sigma}^2 = \frac{1}{n - p} \|x - X\hat{a}\|^2
$$</p>
<p>Thus:
$$
\mathrm{Var}(\hat{a}) \approx \hat{\sigma}^2 (X^T X)^{-1}
$$</p>
<hr>
<h3 id="4.3-Confidence-Intervals-for-Coefficients">4.3 Confidence Intervals for Coefficients<a class="anchor-link" href="#4.3-Confidence-Intervals-for-Coefficients">&#182;</a></h3><p>For each $i$:
$$
\hat{a}_i \sim \mathcal{N}\left(a_i, \ \hat{\sigma}^2 [(X^T X)^{-1}]_{ii}\right)
$$</p>
<p>Confidence interval:
$$
\hat{a}_i \ \pm \ z_{\alpha/2} \cdot \sqrt{\hat{\sigma}^2 [(X^T X)^{-1}]_{ii}}
$$</p>
<p>For finite samples, replace $z_{\alpha/2}$ with $t_{\alpha/2,\, n-p}$.</p>
<hr>
<h3 id="4.4-Confidence-Interval-for-Prediction">4.4 Confidence Interval for Prediction<a class="anchor-link" href="#4.4-Confidence-Interval-for-Prediction">&#182;</a></h3><p>Let:
$$
x_t^{(lag)} = [x_{t-1}, \dots, x_{t-p}]
$$</p>
<p>Then:
$$
\hat{x}_t = x_t^{(lag)} \hat{a}
$$</p>
<p>and:
$$
\mathrm{Var}(\hat{x}_t) = \hat{\sigma}^2 \left(1 + x_t^{(lag)} (X^T X)^{-1} (x_t^{(lag)})^T \right)
$$</p>
<p>Thus:
$$
\hat{x}_t \ \pm \ z_{\alpha/2} \cdot \sqrt{\hat{\sigma}^2 \left(1 + x_t^{(lag)} (X^T X)^{-1} (x_t^{(lag)})^T \right)}
$$</p>
<hr>

</div>
