<h2 id="5----Stationarity-Condition">5 -  Stationarity Condition<a class="anchor-link" href="#5----Stationarity-Condition">&#182;</a></h2><p>The characteristic polynomial for the $AR(p)$ process is the following:
$$\phi(z) = 1-a_1 z - a_2 z^2 - \dots - a_p z^p$$
By a theorem, the process is stationariy if and only if
$$\forall z, \ (\phi(z) = 0 \implies | z | &gt; 1) .$$</p>
<p>That is, verifying stationarity is equivalent to verifying that all roots of the characteristic polynomial lie outside the unit circle.</p>
<p>(Note: the stationarity referred to here is weak stationarity.)</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
